        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 2:54PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 254 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Andover, or 22 miles south of Ashtabula, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Andover and Cherry Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
